**Statement:**
> There is an absolute constant `M ∈ ℝ` (the Meissel–Mertens constant,
> `M ≈ 0.2614972128…`) such that, for all `t ≥ 2`,
>     ∑_{p ≤ t, p prime} 1/p = log log t + M + O(1/log t).

