  -- a's primes ≤ past_cutoff ≤ exp(y_k^{A-1}).  For k ≥ 1, by scale_H
  -- (paper line 1933): y_target = y_{k+1} ≥ exp(y_k^A) > y_k^{A-1}, so
  -- exp(y_k^{A-1}) < exp(y_target).  Hence a's primes < future_lower_floor,
